
Overview of noun admonition

The noun admonition has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                     
1. (3) admonition, monition, warning, word of advice -- (cautionary advice about something imminent (especially imminent danger or other unpleasantness); "a letter of admonition about the dangers of immorality"; "the warning was to beware of surprises"; "his final word of advice was not to play with matches")
2. admonition, admonishment, monition -- (a firm rebuke)
